26. Use image.asset to add image in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

In Flutter, the Image.asset widget is used to display images stored locally in the project (assets folder).

Used for adding images from app resources
Requires image path to be declared in pubspec.yaml
Common for logos, icons, UI images


💻 Steps to Use Image.asset
Create an assets/images folder
Add your image (e.g., sample.png)
Update pubspec.yaml:

// pubsec.yaml

flutter:
  assets:
    - assets/images/sample.png


//main code 
 

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ImageAssetExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ImageAssetExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Image.asset Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Image.asset(
          'assets/images/sample.png',
          width: 200,
          height: 200,
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
